captions.text: [MUSIC PLAYING]
-Hey, everyone.

I'm Mindy from Cute
Girls Hairstyles.

And you can see that today I
have an extra special guest.

This is actually
my niece, Aniston.

And a few days ago she
was here sleeping over

with my daughters, and
she was like, I really
want to be in a hair video.

So we decided that
this tutorial would

be perfect on her
lovely blond hair.

And we are going to show you
how to do the hair-wrapped rope
braid.
So let's get to it.

So to begin with,
we're just going

to pick up all of Ani's
gorgeous blond hair,

and we're going to
pull it to the side.

And I'm literally wanting
it to stay pretty soft,

so I'm just finger
combing through her hair.

And when you get it
the way you want,

you're going to aim for
right here below her ear

so that it's going to give
you a nice side ponytail.
And secure it with an elastic.

Now I'm going to go ahead and
section off a little piece
right here near the front.

And we're going to use
that piece, ultimately,
to wrap the elastic.

But with the remainder
of the ponytail,
you divide it into two pieces.

And it's called a rope braid,
but it's really a rope twist.

What you're going
to do is you're

going to twist to the
right with both pieces.
So I'm going to the right.

And then you're going to cross
them over each other going
to the left.

And what this does is it just
tightens the twist a little bit

so that when you put
the elastic in the hair,
they actually stay twisted.

And you can see that, even
as I work down her ponytail,

I'm still giving it
a right little twist.

See the right little
twist before I cross over
to the left.

And when I get to
the end, I'm just

going to secure it
with an elastic that
matches her hair color.

And there we have
our cute little--

see how I can let it go and it
just stays nice and twisted?
That's perfect.

Now with this extra
piece of hair,

I'm just going to take it
and wrap it up and over
her hair elastic.

And this is just
going to help us

hide that hair elastic,
which is perfect.

And when I get to where
I'm running out of hair--

and I'm going to
just use a bobby pin

and secure that hair-- and then
just tuck those little ends up

and under the rest of her hair
so it's all nice and hidden.

And we have this
very cute-- and then

you can just go
back and loosen it

if you want to make it
very soft and pretty.

And add just a little spritz
of hairspray for any fly-aways
that you have.

And we end up with this
great rope braid twist.

So now another fun
little thing to do

is just take a little
piece of leather--

I think this will
look really cute--

and just wrap it on
the end of the hair.
And then just tie it.

And I just think adding a
little piece of leather--

cut the uneven ends-- just
makes it add a little more pop.

So we hope that you guys
will follow us on Instagram--
-At CuteGirlsHairstyles--
-Yes.

And we will see
you guys next time.
Bye, guys.
-Bye.
[MUSIC PLAYING]

-Left side, and just
cross the [INAUDIBLE].

And last but not least, the
last layer isn't [INAUDIBLE].
Pick up the extra hair.
[INAUDIBLE]
